  description: 
  chapters:
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Devastation of Locusts'
      title: The Devastation of Locusts
      number: 1
      content: '  The word of the Lord that came to Joel, the son of Pethuel.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Hear this, O elders,Listen closely, all inhabitants of the land!Has
        such a thing as this occurred in your days,Or even in the days of your fathers?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Tell your children about it,And let your children tell their children,And
        their children the next generation.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'What the gnawing locust has left, the swarming locust has eaten;And
        what the swarming locust has left, the creeping locust has eaten;And what
        the creeping locust has left, the stripping locust has eaten [in judgment
        of Judah].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Awake [from your intoxication], you drunkards, and weep;Wail, all
        you drinkers of wine,Because of the [fresh] sweet wineThat is cut off from
        your mouth.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'For a [pagan and hostile] nation has invaded My land [like locusts],Mighty
        and without number;Its teeth are the teeth of a lion,And it has the fangs
        of a lioness.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'It has made My vine (My people) a waste and object of horror,And
        splintered and broken My fig tree.It has stripped them completely bare and
        thrown them away;Their branches have become white.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Wail like a virgin [bride] clothed with sackclothFor the bridegroom
        of her youth [who has died].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'The [daily] grain offering and the drink offering are cut offFrom
        the house of the Lord;The priests mournWho minister to the Lord.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'The field is ruined,The ground mourns;For the grain is ruined,The
        new wine is dried up,The fresh oil fails.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Be ashamed, O farmers;Wail, O vinedressers,For the wheat and for
        the barley,Because the harvest of the field has perished.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'The vine dries upAnd the fig tree fails;The pomegranate, the palm
        also, and the apple tree,All the trees of the field dry up,Indeed, joy dries
        up and withdrawsFrom the sons of men.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: Starvation and Drought'
      title: Starvation and Drought
      number: 13
      content: 'Clothe yourselves with sackclothAnd lament (cry out in grief), O
        priests;Wail, O ministers of the altar!Come, spend the night in sackcloth
        [and pray without ceasing],O ministers of my God,For the grain offering and
        the drink offeringAre withheld from the house of your God.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Consecrate a fast,Proclaim a solemn assembly,Gather the eldersAnd
        all the inhabitants of the landTo the house of the Lord your God,And cry
        out to the Lord [in penitent pleadings].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Alas for the day!For the [judgment] day of the Lord is at hand,And
        it will come [upon the nation] as a destruction from the Almighty.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Has not the food been cut off before our eyes,Joy and gladness from
        the house of our God?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'The seeds [of grain] shrivel under the clods,The storehouses are
        desolate and empty,The barns are in ruinsBecause the grain is dried up.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'How the animals groan!The herds of cattle are bewildered and wander
        aimlesslyBecause they have no pasture;Even the flocks of sheep suffer.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'O Lord, I cry out to You,For fire has devoured the pastures of the
        wilderness,And the flame has burned up all the trees of the field.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: Even the wild animals pant [in longing] for You;For the water brooks
        are dried upAnd fire has consumed the pastures of the wilderness.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Terrible Visitation'
      title: The Terrible Visitation
      number: 1
      content: '  Blow the trumpet in Zion [warning of impending judgment],Sound
        an alarm on My holy mountain [Zion]!Let all the inhabitants of the land tremble
        and shudder in fear,For the [judgment] day of the Lord is coming;It is close
        at hand,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'A day of darkness and gloom,A day of clouds and of thick [dark] mist,Like
        the dawn spread over the mountains;There is a [pagan, hostile] people numerous
        and mighty,The like of which has never been beforeNor will be again afterwardEven
        for years of many generations.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Before them a fire devours,And behind them a flame burns;Before them
        the land is like the Garden of Eden,But behind them a desolate wilderness;And
        nothing at all escapes them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Their appearance is like the appearance of horses,And they run like
        war horses.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Like the noise of chariotsThey leap on the tops of the mountains,Like
        the crackling of a flame of fire devouring the stubble,Like a mighty people
        set in battle formation.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Before them the people are in anguish;All faces become pale [with
        terror].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'They run like warriors;They climb the wall like soldiers.They each
        march [straight ahead] in line,And they do not deviate from their paths.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'They do not crowd each other;Each one marches in his path.When they
        burst through the defenses (weapons),They do not break ranks.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'They rush over the city,They run on the wall;They climb up into the
        houses,They enter at the windows like a thief.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'The earth quakes before them,The heavens tremble,The sun and the
        moon grow darkAnd the stars lose their brightness.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'The Lord utters His voice before His army,For His camp is very great,Because
        strong and powerful is he who [obediently] carries out His word.For the day
        of the Lord is indeed great and very terrible [causing dread];Who can endure
        it?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "\u201CEven now,\u201D says the Lord,\u201CTurn and come to Me with
        all your heart [in genuine repentance],With fasting and weeping and mourning
        [until every barrier is removed and the broken fellowship is restored];  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Rip your heart to pieces [in sorrow and contrition] and not your
        garments.\u201DNow return [in repentance] to the Lord your God,For He is
        gracious and compassionate,Slow to anger, abounding in lovingkindness [faithful
        to His covenant with His people];And He relents [His sentence of] evil [when
        His people genuinely repent].  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Who knows whether He will relent [and revoke your sentence],And leave
        a blessing behind Him,Even a grain offering and a drink offering [from the
        bounty He provides you]For the Lord your God?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Blow a trumpet in Zion [warning of impending judgment],Dedicate a
        fast [as a day of restraint and humility], call a solemn assembly.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Gather the people, sanctify the congregation,Assemble the elders,Gather
        the children and the nursing infants.Let the bridegroom come out of his roomAnd
        the bride out of her bridal chamber. [No one is excused from the assembly.]  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: Deliverance Promised'
      title: Deliverance Promised
      number: 17
      content: "Let the priests, the ministers of the Lord,Weep between the porch
        and the altar,And let them say, \u201CHave compassion and spare Your people,
        O Lord,And do not make Your inheritance (Israel) an object of ridicule,Or
        a [humiliating] byword among the [Gentile] nations.Why should they say among
        the peoples,\u2018Where is their God?\u2019\u2009\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Then the Lord will be jealous for His land [ready to defend it since
        it is rightfully and uniquely His]And will have compassion on His people
        [and will spare them].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "The Lord will answer and say to His people,\u201CBehold, I am going
        to send you grain and new wine and oil,And you will be satisfied in full
        with them;And I will never again make you an object of ridicule among the
        [Gentile] nations.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "But I will remove the northern army far away from you,And I will
        drive it into a parched and desolate land,With its forward guard into the
        eastern sea (Dead Sea)And with its rear guard into the western sea (Mediterranean
        Sea).And its stench will arise and its foul odor of decay will come up [this
        is the fate of the northern army in the final day of the Lord],For He has
        done great things.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Do not fear, O land; be glad and rejoice,For the Lord has done great
        things!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Do not be afraid, you animals of the field,For the pastures of the
        wilderness have turned green;The tree has produced its fruit,And the fig
        tree and the vine have yielded in full.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'So rejoice, O children of Zion,And delight in the Lord, your God;For
        He has given you the early [autumn] rain in vindicationAnd He has poured
        down the rain for you,The early [autumn] rain and the late [spring] rain,
        as before.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'And the threshing floors shall be full of grain,And the vats shall
        overflow with new wine and oil.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "\u201CAnd I will compensate you for the yearsThat the swarming locust
        has eaten,The creeping locust, the stripping locust, and the gnawing locust\u2014My
        great army which I sent among you.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'You will have plenty to eat and be satisfiedAnd praise the name of
        the Lord your GodWho has dealt wondrously with you;And My people shall never
        be put to shame.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: The Promise of the Spirit'
      title: The Promise of the Spirit
      number: 27
      content: 'And you shall know [without any doubt] that I am in the midst of
        Israel [to protect and bless you],And that I am the Lord your God,And there
        is no other;My people will never be put to shame.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "\u201CIt shall come about after thisThat I shall pour out My Spirit
        on all mankind;And your sons and your daughters will prophesy,Your old men
        will dream dreams,Your young men will see visions.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: The Day of the Lord'
      title: The Day of the Lord
      number: 29
      content: 'Even on the male and female servantsI will pour out My Spirit in
        those days.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'I will show signs and wonders [displaying My power] in the heavens
        and on the earth,Blood and fire and columns of smoke.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'The sun will be turned into darknessAnd the moon into bloodBefore
        the great and terrible day of the Lord comes.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: And it shall come about that whoever calls on the name of the LordWill
        be saved [from the coming judgment]For on Mount Zion and in JerusalemThere
        will be those who escape,As the Lord has said,Even among the remnant [of
        survivors] whom the Lord calls.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Nations Will Be Judged'
      title: The Nations Will Be Judged
      number: 1
      content: "  \u201CFor behold, in those [climactic] days and at that time,When
        I restore the fortunes of Judah and Jerusalem,  "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'I will gather together all the [Gentile] nations [that were hostile
        to My people]And bring them down into the Valley of Jehoshaphat (the Lord
        has judged).And there I will deal with them and enter into judgment with
        them thereFor [their treatment of] My people, My inheritance, Israel,Whom
        they have scattered among the nations,And [because] they have encroached
        on My land and divided it up.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'They have also cast lots for My people,And have traded a boy for
        a prostituteAnd have sold a girl for wine that they may drink.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Moreover, what are you to Me, O Tyre and Sidon and all the [five
        small] regions of Philistia? Will you pay Me back for something [I have supposedly
        done to you]? Even if you do pay Me back, I will swiftly and speedily return
        your deed [of retaliation] on your own head. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Because you have taken My silver and My gold and have carried My
        precious treasures to your temples and palaces, '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'and have sold the children of Judah and the children of Jerusalem
        to the Greeks, so that you may send them far away from their territory, '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'behold, I am going to stir them up from the place where you have
        sold them [and return them to their land], and I shall return your action
        [of retaliation] on your own head. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Also I will sell your sons and your daughters into the hand of the
        children of Judah, and they will sell them to the Sabeans, to a distant nation,\u201D
        for the Lord has spoken.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Proclaim this among the [pagan] nations:Prepare a war! Stir up the
        mighty men!Let all the men of war come near, let them come up!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Beat your plowshares into swordsAnd your pruning hooks into spears;Let
        the weak say, \u201CI am strong!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Hurry and come, all you surrounding nations,And gather yourselves
        there;Bring down, O Lord, Your mighty ones (Your warriors).  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Let the nations be stirred [to action]And come up to the Valley of
        Jehoshaphat,For there I will sit to judge and punishAll the surrounding nations.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Put in the sickle [of judgment], for the harvest is ripe;Come, tread
        [the grapes], for the wine press is full;The vats overflow, for the wickedness
        [of the people] is great.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Multitudes, multitudes in the valley of decision (judgment)!For the
        day of the Lord is near in the valley of decision [when judgment is executed].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'The sun and the moon grow darkAnd the stars lose their brightness.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'The Lord thunders and roars from ZionAnd utters His voice from Jerusalem
        [in judgment of His enemies],And the heavens and the earth tremble and shudder;But
        the Lord is a refuge for His peopleAnd a stronghold [of protection] to the
        children of Israel.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: Judah Will Be Blessed'
      title: Judah Will Be Blessed
      number: 17
      content: 'Then you will know and understand fully that I am the Lord your God,Dwelling
        in Zion, My holy mountain.Then Jerusalem will be holy,And strangers [who
        do not belong] will no longer pass through it.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'And in that dayThe mountains will drip with sweet wineAnd the hills
        will flow with milk;And all the brooks and riverbeds of Judah will flow with
        water,And a fountain will go out from the house of the LordTo water the [desert]
        Valley of Shittim.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Egypt will become a waste,And Edom will become a desolate wilderness,Because
        of their violence against the children of Judah,In whose land they have shed
        innocent blood.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'But Judah shall be inhabited foreverAnd Jerusalem from generation
        to generation.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: And I shall avenge their blood which I have not avenged,For the Lord
        dwells in Zion.
      comments: []
